To do so, create a java file inside Eclipse (I'm working with it, so I know but not about other IDEs).
Download mysql-connector.jar file and paste it inside the src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/lib/mysql-connector.jar and right click on the connector => then on Build Path
=> then on Add to Build Path and you are done.

Now, you do some code..

// Load class
Class.forName("com.mysql.jdbc.Driver");
// Create Connection
Connection con = DriverManager.getConnection("jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/<DB_name>","root","<password>");
// Create Statements
Statement stmt = con.createStatement();
// Create String
String sql = "create table hello(id int,name text)";
stmt.executeUpdate(sql);
// Close the Connection
con.close();
System.out.println("Amazing! Table Created");

all inside main method. Import Required Packages.
